<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8" /><title>Randomizing with Arrays</title><style type="text/css">body {	font-family: courier, monospace;	color:#FF6633;	}	.instructions {	color: #666666;	font-family: georgia, serif;	}	code {	color: #444;	font-weight: bold;	font-size: 1.1em;}</style></head><body><header><h1 class="instructions">Randomizing with Arrays</h1></header><article><h2 class="instructions">Using <code>array_rand()</code></h2><p class="instructions">I have created an array for you using the <code>array()</code> function. What kind of array is it?</p><p class="instructions">Create a "random phrase" generator with the <code>rand_array()</code> function and the array below that I have built for you.</p><?php$phrase = array('Mary had a little lamb.', 'Little Boy Blue, come blow your horn.', 'Hey diddle diddle, the cat and the fiddle.', 'Mistress Mary, quite contrary, how does your garden grow?', 'Jack Sprat could eat no fat, his wife could eat no lean.', 'Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall. Humpty Dumpty had a great fall.', 'Jack and Jill went up the hill to fetch a pail of water.');//creating a random phrase of the moment script$random_key = array_rand($phrase);//echo $phrase[$random_key];echo 'Here is your random nursery rhyme phrase of the moment: <br />';$random_key = array_rand($phrase);$random_phrase = $phrase[$random_key];echo $random_phrase;?><h2 class="instructions">Random Snack of the Moment</h2><p class="instructions">Now that you have created a random phrase generator, create a random snack generator for a "snack of the moment." You will need to build the array yourself using the <code>array()</code> function. Your array elements are the following snacks: Doritos, Cheesy Poofs, pork rinds, Good 'n' Plenty, Atomic Fire Balls, wasabi peas, Raisinettes, apple slices, carrot sticks, Ritz crackers.</p><p class="instructions">Output your random snack in a sentence that says, "Your random snack of the moment is (random snack)."</p><!-- write script here --><?php$snack = array('Doritos', 'Chessy Poofs', 'pork rinds', 'Good \'n\' Plenty', 'Atomic Fire Balls', 'wasabi peas', 'Raisinettes', 'apple slices', 'carrot sticks', 'Ritz crackers');$random_key = array_rand($snack);//echo $phrase[$random_key];$random_snack = $snack[$random_key];echo 'Your random snack of the moment is '.$random_snack.'.';?><h2 class="instructions">Random Drink of the Moment</h2><p class="instructions">Now create an associative array for a random drink of the moment using the <code>array()</code> function. You'll have five categories of drink: carbonated, alcoholic, sickly sweet, caffeinated and milky. Your carbonated drink is Fanta, your alcoholic drink is Cap'n Morgan Spiced Rum, your sickly sweet drink is Shirley Temple, your caffeinated drink is espresso and your milky drink is chocolate milk.</p><p class="instructions">Output your random drink in a sentence that says, "Your random drink of the moment is: (random drink). That drink is (descriptor from key)."</p><!-- write script here --><?php$drink = array(	'carbonated' => 'Fanta',	'alcoholic' => 'Cap\'n Morgan Spiced Rum', 	'slickly sweet' => 'Shirley Temple', 	'caffeinated' => 'espresso',	'milky' => 'chocolate milk'	);$random_key = array_rand($drink);//echo $phrase[$random_key];$random_drink = $drink[$random_key];echo 'Your random drink of the moment is '.$random_drink.'.';?><h2 class="instructions">Homework: Random Image Generator</h2><p class="instructions">In addition to any of the exercises above that you have not finished before the end of class, you need to create a random image generator that will display one of the images in the images directory on the page below this paragraph as homework for Wednesday.</p><ol class="instructions"><li>What html needs to be in the page to display an image? What is needed for valid html5? What is recommended for "best practices?"</li><li>What kind of array will you build? An indexed array or an associative array? Why?</li><li>What will the array elements (array objects) be?</li><li>How will you output the value for the array elements into the necessary markup for image display?</li></ol><?php$image = array('blue.gif', 'yellow.gif', 'green.gif', 'orange.gif', 'pink.gif', 'red.gif');$random_key = array_rand($image);$random_image = $image[$random_key];?><img src="/php424/8arrays/images/<?php echo $random_image; ?>" alt="colored rectangle" /></article></body></html>